{"parentUuid":"238bd083-0806-4057-85ae-36475aaef064","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa91a4ccd0eafabe2","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs5fVdryhgJdqbMs5zyp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SaE1K5sYHdTz1p1fDDUHdo","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":46,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7741,"cache_read_input_tokens":27751,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7741,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs5fUdqUR6uK7E5hzWxY","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"6850d557-4be9-4aec-9536-6741238932c0","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:03:02.148Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"6850d557-4be9-4aec-9536-6741238932c0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"aa91a4ccd0eafabe2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SaE1K5sYHdTz1p1fDDUHdo","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: clean\n3\tran_at: 2026-07-09T18:54:55Z\n4\tscope: diff\n5\tsince_commit: 43da3203feb5e9be3d7684992b47209188d328b0\n6\tcritical_count: 0\n7\twarning_count: 2\n8\tfixed_count: 0\n9\ttotal_findings: 5\n10\tsemgrep_findings: 2\n11\tosv_findings: 2\n12\tcheckov_findings: 0\n13\ttrivy_findings: 0\n14\tstride_mechanisms_verified: 8\n15\tstride_mechanisms_missing: 0\n16\tstride_new_threats: 0\n17\t---\n18\t\n19\t# Security report — usage CSV export (`GET /v1/usage/export`)\n20\t\n21\t**Verdict: clean.** No critical findings remain. The change set adds one read-only\n22\tstreaming CSV endpoint over the existing `usage_rollup` table plus its schema, service,\n23\trepository queries, CSV-encoding facade, and tests. Every planned STRIDE mitigation is\n24\tpresent *and* effective (per-mechanism efficacy checked, not just presence); the two\n25\tSemgrep ERROR hits are verified false positives (fully parameterized queries); the one OSV\n26\tCVE is a dev-only, below-floor moderate; and no new attack surface escaped the threat model.\n27\t\n28\t## Tools run\n29\t\n30\t| Tool | Scope | Result |\n31\t|---|---|---|\n32\t| Semgrep (`auto`, `p/secrets`, `p/owasp-top-ten`, `p/python`) | 11 code-shaped changed files | 2 ERROR (verified false positives) |\n33\t| OSV Scanner | full manifest (`.`) | 1 unique CVE (2 aliased ids) — pytest, dev dep, moderate |\n34\t| Gitleaks (`dir`) | full tree | 125 raw hits — all `.venv/` dependency data or test fixtures (out of scope / FP) |\n35\t| ASVS Tier-1 SAST (`asvs-sast.sh`) | diff | 0 critical, 0 warning |\n36\t| Lockfile / supply-chain (`lockfile-check.sh`) | change set | clean (exit 0) |\n37\t| SBOM (`generate-sbom.sh`) | project | produced — CycloneDX, 65 components |\n38\t| ast-grep structural rules | change set | **NOT RUN — ast-grep unavailable on PATH** (disclosed skip; see note below) |\n39\t| Checkov / Trivy | n/a | no `infra/` dir and no Dockerfile/image in the change set — not applicable |\n40\t\n41\t**ast-grep disclosed skip (F-M4-5):** the diff touches SQL/queries and async entrypoints, so\n42\tthe `ast-grep-rules` pack was invoked, but the wrapper exited 2 — `ast-grep not on PATH`\n43\t(`npm install -g @ast-grep/cli`). This is a DISCLOSED skip, not a silent one. The two\n44\tsyntax-shaped concerns ast-grep would have flagged were both verified manually instead: (1)\n45\tthe `text()`+f-string SQL — confirmed the interpolated `where_clause` is built only from\n46\tfixed string literals in `_export_filter_clause_and_params`, all values bound; (2) KDF/blocking\n47\tcalls on the async event loop — the export path does no KDF and uses only `await`-ed async DB\n48\tcalls (`session.stream`, `count_usage_rollups`, `scoped_transaction`). ast-grep findings are\n49\tadvisory-only regardless, so this skip does not affect any count or gate conjunct.\n50\t\n51\t## Complete findings inventory\n52\t\n53\t| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n54\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n55\t| 1 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py:129` | reported-only (verified false positive) |\n56\t| 2 | semgrep | `python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text` | ERROR | no | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py:161` | reported-only (verified false positive) |\n57\t| 3 | osv | `PYSEC-2026-1845` / `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (one vuln, two aliases) | Moderate (CVSS ~6.8) | no | `pytest==8.3.4` (dev dependency) | action-required (below 7.0 floor — human decides) |\n58\t| 4 | gitleaks | `generic-api-key` (125 raw hits) | n/a | no | `.venv/**` (dependency data) + `tests/**` fixtures | reported-only (out of scope / false positive) |\n59\t| 5 | manual-6d | RLS `FORCE` inert on `usage_rollup` (ASVS 8.2.x backstop) | Low | no | migration `0002` (pre-existing, not in diff) | reported-only (accepted risk R2 / Open Q3; primary control effective) |\n60\t\n61\t`total_findings = 5`. No row is omitted on grounds of low severity, non-exploitability, or\n62\tnon-remediation.\n63\t\n64\t### Finding 1 & 2 — Semgrep `avoid-sqlalchemy-text` (false positive)\n65\t\n66\tThe rule fires on any `text()` call carrying an f-string. Both hits are safe:\n67\t`count_usage_rollups` (line 129) and `stream_usage_rollups` (line 161) interpolate only\n68\t`where_clause`, the return of `_export_filter_clause_and_params` (line ~74), which is\n69\t`\" AND \".join(clauses)` where every `clause` is a **fixed string literal**\n70\t(`\"api_key_id = :api_key_id\"`, `\"customer_id = :customer_id\"`, …). No filter *value* ever\n71\tenters the SQL string — all values travel as bound parameters in the `params` dict. The\n72\t`ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC` is likewise a fixed literal, never\n73\tclient-derived. There is no injection vector; both are recorded as reported-only false\n74\tpositives and deliberately **not** folded into `critical_count`. (They remain counted in\n75\t`semgrep_findings: 2` so the reconcile hook's re-count of the artifact matches.)\n76\t\n77\t### Finding 3 — pytest tmpdir CVE (OSV)\n78\t\n79\t`pytest==8.3.4` is affected by a `tmpdir`-handling issue (`PYSEC-2026-1845` /\n80\t`GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g`, one vulnerability under two database ids). CVSS 3.1 vector\n81\t`AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:L` ≈ 6.8 (GitHub: **Moderate**), local vector, **below the\n82\tdeploy gate's 7.0 High/Critical floor**. pytest is a **dev/test-only** dependency, never on\n83\tthe request path. Reported, not auto-fixed (per policy — dependency bumps are not made here).\n84\tSafe upgrade recorded in Action required.\n85\t\n86\t### Finding 4 — Gitleaks hits (all out of scope / false positive)\n87\t\n88\tGitleaks flagged 125 strings. Every hit resolves to either `.venv/**` third-party library\n89\texample/test data (AWS botocore fixtures, etc. — dependency tree, not the change set) or a\n90\ttest-fixture line such as `metric=\"api_calls\", idempotency_key=\"a\"` in\n91\t`tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py:117` (the `generic-api-key` regex misfiring\n92\ton adjacent kwargs). Presented API keys in tests come from the `make_api_key()` fixture, not\n93\thardcoded literals. No real secret is committed in the change set. The independent\n94\tchange-set secrets grep (6a), Semgrep `p/secrets`, and the ASVS Tier-1 SAST all agree: zero\n95\tsecrets in source.\n96\t\n97\t### Finding 5 — RLS `FORCE` backstop inert on `usage_rollup` (pre-existing)\n98\t\n99\tThe `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS policy (migration `0002`) is `ENABLE ROW LEVEL\n100\tSECURITY` **without `FORCE`**, and the app role (`meterly_app`) owns the table — a table\n101\towner bypasses non-`FORCE` RLS, so the RLS *backstop* is effectively inert for the app role.\n102\tThis is disclosed in the plan (accepted risk R2, Open Q3), pre-dates this feature, and\n103\taffects `GET /v1/usage` identically. Critically, tenant isolation for the export does **not\n104\trely on RLS** — the primary control is the mandatory explicit `api_key_id = principal.api_key_id`\n105\tpredicate on both new queries (verified present, see 6b/6d), which is effective. Recorded as a\n106\twarning / accepted risk; the recommended follow-up is a migration adding `ALTER TABLE\n107\tusage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` (mirroring `0003` for `quotas`). This feature does not\n108\tworsen the condition and does not depend on RLS for its isolation.\n109\t\n110\t## Manual checks (steps 6a–6g)\n111\t\n112\t- **6a Secrets:** change-set grep clean; `.env` and `.envrc` gitignored, no `.env` tracked;\n113\t  no secrets in `PROJECT.md`/`CLAUDE.md`/configs. No hardcoded credential in source.\n114\t- **6b Row-level security / IDOR:** both new queries (`count_usage_rollups`,\n115\t  `stream_usage_rollups`) scope by `api_key_id` **first** as a mandatory predicate sourced\n116\t  from the authenticated principal; `api_key_id` is absent from the request schema and\n117\t  `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects a client-supplied one. IDOR/BOLA closed. ✓\n118\t- **6c Input / output sanitization:** query params validated by `UsageExportQueryParams`\n119\t  (anchored-allowlist `constr` reused from `events.py`, `AwareDatetime`, `[now-90d, now+1h]`\n120\t  bounds, `from<=to`, `extra=\"forbid\"`). SQL sink parameterized (bound params, fixed-literal\n121\t  clauses). CSV sink: `escape_csv_text_cell` neutralizes formula-injection on `customer_id`\n122\t  and `metric` (the only attacker-influenced cells; numeric/timestamp are server-generated),\n123\t  plus `Content-Disposition: attachment` + inherited `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`. ✓\n124\t- **6d STRIDE mechanism verification (presence + efficacy):** all 8 named mechanisms present\n125\t  AND effective — see table below.\n126\t- **6e Log-sink safety:** the `usage.export` / `usage.export.rejected` events log only opaque\n127\t  `api_key_id` (int), row counts, and *presence booleans* (`filtered_by_customer`, …) — no raw\n128\t  `customer_id`/`metric`, so no log-forging newline surface and no PII/secret in logs. ✓\n129\t- **6f STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation:** every new surface in the diff\n130\t  (the `GET /v1/usage/export` entry point, the CSV→spreadsheet boundary, two new\n131\t  `usage_rollup` queries, the streamed `text/csv` body, the new `usage.export` log event, the\n132\t  any-authenticated-key authz surface) is already covered by a threat-model entry.\n133\t  `stride_new_threats: 0`; the STRIDE delta addendum is empty.\n134\t- **6g ASVS 5.0.0:** triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16 verified at L1+L2 —\n135\t  reconciled, see below.\n136\t\n137\t### 6d — STRIDE mechanism table (presence + efficacy)\n138\t\n139\t| STRIDE | Mechanism | Evidence | Efficacy check |\n140\t|---|---|---|---|\n141\t| Spoofing | `require_api_key` on route | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py:52` (`Depends(require_api_key)`) | ✓ 401 before handler; reused unchanged facade |\n142\t| Tampering (SQL) | allowlist validation + bound-param SQL + fixed ORDER BY | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py:129,161` | ✓ no value in SQL string; ORDER BY fixed literal |\n143\t| Tampering (CSV) | `escape_csv_text_cell` at encoding sink | `src/api/csv_export.py:29` | ✓ escapes leading `= + - @ \\t \\r`; reachable leading-`-` case covered |\n144\t| Repudiation | one `usage.export` audit log in `finally` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` (finally block) | ✓ fires on completion and on client disconnect |\n145\t| Info Disclosure (tenant) | mandatory `api_key_id` filter (primary control) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` (`api_key_id = :api_key_id` first clause) | ✓ effective; does not rely on the inert RLS backstop (F5) |\n146\t| Info Disclosure (PII/logs/errors) | minimal 4-col projection, booleans-not-values logging, generic error envelope, UTC-only filename, `no-store` | `usage_repo.py` (`UsageRollupExportRecord`), service log, `_export_filename` (routes:63), `src/api/middleware.py` (existing) | ✓ no tenant id in filename; no raw PII logged |\n147\t| Denial of Service | pre-flight count→422 + `LIMIT 100000` + constant-memory stream + Tier-2 per-key throttle | `usage_export_service.py` (`prepare_export`, `_drain`), `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` | ✓ binding throttle is **identity-keyed** (Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`), so it actually limits per-caller; no event-loop stall (async DB only) |\n148\t| Elevation of Privilege | `api_key_id`/`scope` absent from schema + `extra=\"forbid\"`; id from principal | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | ✓ mass-assignment rejected; not scope-gated so nothing to escalate |\n149\t\n150\t**Topology efficacy note:** the *binding* rate limit for this authenticated route is the\n151\tTier-2 per-`api_key_id` bucket (correctly identity-keyed — two tenants behind one NAT/ALB get\n152\tindependent buckets), so it is not subject to the client-IP-behind-ALB single-bucket pitfall.\n153\tThe pre-auth Tier-1 IP throttle's ALB client-IP derivation is a pre-existing app-wide\n154\tcondition, not introduced or depended upon by this feature.\n155\t\n156\t### 6g — ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation\n157\t\n158\tPlan `## ASVS Compliance` block present. Triggered chapters (L1+L2 universal):\n159\t**V1** (CSV/formula output encoding, SQL parameterization — ✓ `csv_export.py`, `usage_repo.py`),\n160\t**V2** (Pydantic allowlist validation, `extra=\"forbid\"`, window bounds, throttle — ✓),\n161\t**V4** (REST status codes 422/401/500, content-type — ✓),\n162\t**V6** (reused API-key split-token + Argon2id verify — ✓ inherited),\n163\t**V8** (tenant isolation via mandatory `api_key_id` predicate, BOLA closed — ✓, overlaps 6b),\n164\t**V13** (no secrets in code, minimal error disclosure — ✓),\n165\t**V14** (minimal projection, no tenant id in filename per 14.3.2, `Cache-Control: no-store` — ✓),\n166\t**V16** (structured audit log without PII, generic fail-closed error envelope per 16.5.x — ✓, overlaps 6e).\n167\t`n/a`: V5 (no file upload — the feature *emits* a download), V7/V9/V10 (stateless API-key auth,\n168\tno session/JWT/OAuth), V11 (no new crypto), V12 (TLS at ALB, inherited), V3/V15 (no new frontend).\n169\tNo in-scope L3 items new for this feature. `l1_l2_missing: []`, `l3_in_scope_missing: []`,\n170\t`reconciled: true`.\n171\t\n172\t*Note (plan-audit observation, non-blocking):* the plan's ASVS block labels the n/a chapters\n173\t(V5/V7/V9/V10) as \"waivers.\" These are correctly **n/a determinations** (chapters not\n174\ttriggered by the diff), not waivers of unmet code/config items, so no `waivers.json` entry is\n175\trequired and `asvs.waivers` is empty. No reconciliation impact.\n176\t\n177\t## Input-surface reconciliation\n178\t\n179\tOne input source implemented — `GET /v1/usage/export` query params (`customer_id`, `metric`,\n180\t`from`, `to`). Both controls present: validation contract (`UsageExportQueryParams`) **and**\n181\trate-limit policy (Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`), each traceable to AC4/AC5. `declared: 1,\n182\timplemented: 1, uncontrolled: [], reconciled: true`.\n183\t\n184\t## Data-surface reconciliation\n185\t\n186\tRead-only feature (`new_stored_data: false`) — no new DB table/column, file write, cache\n187\tentry, or export field beyond what the existing ingest path already stores. `classified: 0,\n188\tsensitive: 0, unprotected: [], reconciled: true`.\n189\t\n190\t## Fixes applied\n191\t\n192\tNone. No exploitable or critical-severity hygiene finding required a code change — the two\n193\tSemgrep ERROR hits are verified false positives on fully parameterized queries, and the OSV\n194\tCVE is a report-only dependency finding below the gate floor. `fixed_count: 0`.\n195\t\n196\t## Could not remediate\n197\t\n198\tNone.\n199\t\n200\t## Action required (human decision — not auto-fixed)\n201\t\n202\t- **`pytest` 8.3.4 → 9.0.3** (dev dependency): resolves `PYSEC-2026-1845` /\n203\t  `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (tmpdir handling, CVSS ~6.8 Moderate, local). Below the deploy gate's\n204\t  7.0 floor and off the request path, so it does not block. Bump via `pyproject.toml` +\n205\t  `poetry.lock` when convenient (dependency bumps are performed by the debugging/remediation\n206\t  path, not the security stage).\n207\t\n208\t## STRIDE delta addendum\n209\t\n210\tEmpty — the diff introduces no attack surface that the plan's threat model does not already\n211\tcover (`stride_new_threats: 0`). Every new/changed surface (new route, CSV→spreadsheet\n212\tboundary, two `usage_rollup` queries, streamed CSV body, new log event, any-authenticated-key\n213\tauthz) maps to an existing STRIDE row verified in 6d.\n214\t"}]},"uuid":"0273afd8-90fb-4803-89eb-23f87fdd37e0","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:03:02.182Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6850d557-4be9-4aec-9536-6741238932c0","userType":