{"parentUuid":"9acfe60a-27b1-494b-b208-aa1cbb20e253","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa91a4ccd0eafabe2","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs75Yy59ECkLrcDtzf2t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Remediation re-scan complete. Both output files are consistent and the U-09 reconciliation passes.\n\n**Summary:** Tools: Semgrep (4 findings), OSV (2 aliased ids/1 vuln), Gitleaks, ast-grep 0.44.1 (now installed — structural SQL/async pass ran), ASVS Tier-1 SAST, lockfile-check, SBOM. Scope: diff vs `43da320`, 12 code-shaped files. **Found 7 / fixed 0 / 0 critical remaining → status: clean.**\n\nKey points for this cycle-2 remediation run:\n- **The AC16 perf fix preserved every security invariant.** The `str.translate` deletion table in `src/api/csv_export.py` is semantically identical to the prior per-character filter (same C0 controls stripped, same leading-formula-trigger quoting); `yield_per` in `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` only tunes cursor batch size (constant-memory streaming and fixed-literal WHERE/ORDER BY unchanged, values still bound); `_ROWS_PER_CHUNK` batching in `src/services/usage_export_service.py` changes only when bytes are handed to the ASGI stack. Findings are unchanged from cycle-1 (the Semgrep SQL hit's line moved 161→175).\n- **ast-grep disclosed skip is now closed (F-M4-5).** ast-grep 0.44.1 ran and stamped `scan-log.jsonl`. Its SQL `text()`+f-string rule hit the same two sites Semgrep flags (`usage_repo.py:129,175`) — both confirmed safe (fixed-literal clauses, bound params); its KDF-on-event-loop rule found nothing in the export path. Advisory-only, per the skill boundary — not folded into any count.\n- **Two new low-severity WARNINGs surfaced** because the reconcile hook requires the full code-shaped change set in Semgrep scope, pulling in `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml`: `actions/setup-python@v5` uses a mutable tag instead of a pinned SHA (lines 54, 86). Pre-existing (outside the diff's one-line `--cov-fail-under=85` hunk), non-blocking; recommended follow-up is a SHA pin by the CI owner.\n- **Unchanged carry-overs:** the `pytest==8.3.4` CVE (`PYSEC-2026-1845`/`GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g`, CVSS ~6.8, dev-only, below the 7.0 gate floor — reported, not auto-bumped) and the pre-existing inert RLS `FORCE` backstop on `usage_rollup` (accepted risk R2; primary `api_key_id` tenant predicate is effective).\n- No `infra/`, Dockerfile, or migrations in scope → Checkov/Trivy n/a. STRIDE: 8/8 mechanisms present and effective, 0 new threats. ASVS/input-surface/data-surface all reconciled.\n\nRelevant files:\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-report.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-status.json`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\scan-reconciliation.json` (reconciled: true)"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1714,"cache_read_input_tokens":88301,"output_tokens":1205,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1714},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1205,"cache_read_input_tokens":88301,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1714,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1714,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs75XrbRjfd1N5PpRXjK","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"530a65c6-94a1-42c0-a350-074b27bbfcba","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:21:47.438Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature